cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "Evolving VLM Inference for CharXiv"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Huang
    given-names: Qi
    affiliation: "The University of Chicago"
    email: qihuang@uchicago.edu
repository-code: "https://github.com/QiHuang321/Evolving"
license: MIT
date-released: "2026-03-19"
abstract: >-
  AlphaEvolve-style evolutionary code optimization for VLM chart question
  answering on the CharXiv benchmark. Evolution alone improves a naive
  baseline from 38.3% to 60.9% exact-match accuracy; subsequent post-analysis
  post-processing and targeted verifiers reach 79.7% on the 128-sample
  development subset.
keywords:
  - vision-language-model
  - chart-question-answering
  - evolutionary-search
  - alphaevolve
  - charxiv
  - qwen
